<chapter xml:id="ch-04-indirect-proofs" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Indirect Proofs</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
        The student's go-to proof is most commonly the direct proof, yet there are many methods of 
        proving that do not involve this method - they are broadly described as indirect proofs. In this chapter 
        we will go through a few examples.
    </p>
</introduction>

